race.comment: PAW LINDEN (3) is progressing well and looks close to another win after hitting the frame from Box 1 last run (23.34) at this track. Ran one of the fastest times on the program last start despite finishing in the minors. Top prospect. SOMETHING GOOD (1) has a strong winning strike-rate over this track and trip with four wins and a placing from nine tries. Hit the frame latest (22.21) when third at Ballarat in a Grade 4/5. Suited here and expected to run well. NOSEY PARKER (7) boasts a strong record this journey here with six wins and three minors from 17 tries. Was out of the placings last time (25.64) at Shepparton in a Special conditions H, finishing fourth and beaten 11 lengths. Looks one of the chances. GAS LANTERN (2) placed in a close finish last start - worth some thought.
